# Local product testing

When the user asks to **开始测试**, **联调**, **手工验收**, **回归测试**, **按本地测试规则测**, or otherwise verify product behavior on a running app (not only lint/build/unit tests):

Read and follow **`.cursor/skills/mesa-local-product-test/SKILL.md`** (curl API first, Chrome DevTools MCP for UI, cleanup, pass/fail report).

## No skip unless truly blocked

Default every checklist / regression item to **run** and report **`pass`** or **`fail`**.

**`skip` is forbidden** for convenience, time, “covered by unit”, “hard to automate”, dual-tab/realtime, cache invalidate, or “do later”.

**`skip` allowed only when the item is objectively impossible in this thread**, for example:

- localhost / login / required MCP (Chrome DevTools) unavailable after a real attempt
- missing secrets or env the agent cannot obtain
- user explicitly forbids the only safe way to exercise the path (e.g. no DB wipe when the case *requires* wipe)

Every `skip` **must** state the blocker in one line. Prefer a weaker but real assertion (API shape, HTTP status, unit for retired route) over skip. If the user says **不允许 skip**, treat soft blockers as **fail** or keep trying — do not skip.

